---
import FeatureCard from "./FeatureCard.astro";
---

<section id="features" class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <header class="header">
      <p class="eyebrow">Features</p>
      <h2 class="headline">Built for how agents actually ship code.</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        Every piece of Dynamo exists because something agentic broke in
        practice — context lost across providers, child agents trampling each
        other, diffs auto&#8209;merged before review, plans buried in a chat scroll.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="grid">
      <FeatureCard title="Team agents over MCP" glyph="◆">
        A coordinator session you talk to, with bounded child threads it
        spawns through Dynamo&apos;s built&#8209;in MCP server. Pick the
        provider and model per task — the coordinator routes, the children do
        the work.
      </FeatureCard>

      <FeatureCard title="Board view for real plans" glyph="▤">
        Stored columns for ideas and planned work, derived columns for
        in&#8209;progress, review, and done. Cards link directly to the agent
        thread doing the work, not a Jira mirror updated by hand.
      </FeatureCard>

      <FeatureCard title="Worktree isolation" glyph="⌥">
        Every child agent gets its own Git worktree and branch, auto&#8209;created
        from your repo. Parallel work stops fighting over the same
        files; non&#8209;Git projects fall back to a shared workspace.
      </FeatureCard>

      <FeatureCard title="Fork-able threads" glyph="⑂">
        Branch a conversation when you want to try a different approach
        without losing the working one. Both forks stay live, with their own
        history, worktree, and provider state.
      </FeatureCard>

      <FeatureCard title="Sandbox modes" glyph="◇">
        Run sessions in read&#8209;only, workspace&#8209;write, or full&#8209;access mode.
        Set the leash before the agent runs — not after it has touched the
        wrong directory.
      </FeatureCard>

      <FeatureCard title="Review &amp; apply diffs" glyph="±">
        Child agents propose diffs; nothing merges automatically. You review
        them in Dynamo and apply when they&apos;re right. No surprise commits,
        no mystery rewrites of files you didn&apos;t open.
      </FeatureCard>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .section {
    padding: var(--section-pad-y) var(--gutter);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .section-inner {
    max-width: var(--section-max-w);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .header {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    font-size: var(--eyebrow-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--eyebrow-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .headline {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, 2.6rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .lede {
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
